org.cloudbus.cloudsim.geoweb.web

Class BaseStatGenerator<T extends Cloudlet>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.cloudbus.cloudsim.geoweb.web.BaseStatGenerator<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - - the actual type of the generated CloudLets.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    IGenerator<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    StatGenerator

    public abstract class BaseStatGenerator<T extends Cloudlet>
extends Object
implements IGenerator<T>
    A base class containing the main functionality of a statistical generator of CloutLets. This class generates CloudLets based on the provided statistical distributions for their properties. Random generators are provided in a map, whose keys usually are the constants of the class, as documented below.
    Author:
    nikolay.grozev

      • BaseStatGenerator

        public BaseStatGenerator(Map<String,? extends org.uncommons.maths.number.NumberGenerator<? extends Number>> seqGenerators,
                         double startTime,
                         double endTime,
                         DataItem data)
        Creates a new generator with the specified statistical distributions.
        Parameters:
        randomGenerators - - the statistical distributions to be used for the generation of CloudLets. See the standard keys provided above to see what is usually expected from this map. Inheriting classes may define their own key and values to be used in the factory method. Must not be null.
        startTime - - the start time of the generation. If positive, no web cloudlets with ideal start time before this will be generated.
        startTime - - the end time of the generation. If positive, no web cloudlets with ideal start time after this will be generated.
        data - - the data used by the generator, or null if no data is used.
